<br>
  There's a couple of problems with that theory.<br>
<br>
(1)  We -KNOW- Magister is VS capable.  There is absolutely no doubt in our minds of this fact.<br>
<br>
(2)  The rotation only works because it's fair, and everyone has a chance to join it.  As soon as we exclude a guild, be it Magister or the Flaming Butt Weasels of Doom ,who is capable of taking down VS, then the whole stack of cards comes tumbling down.<br>
<br>
Just like it has now.<br>
<br>
(3)  Most of us know and like people in Magister.  Hell, I'm on good terms with Koryo : ).  If any of you had sent me a tell about it I would have said &quot;Sure, you need to talk to Yenom to arrange it, I'll make sure he knows you're looking for it&quot;.  And I would have done just that. <br>
<br>
(4)  There are public forums to bring this matter up before it gets to the &quot;Ignore common sense and courtesy and pull VS through people buffing to take him&quot; stage.  Others have asked on the public Storm's Fury boards and received an answer in a timely fashion... ironically the whole suituation was clarified there about a day or so before this errupted.  And hell... even a quick flame about how unreasonable the people in the rotation were being would have likely had the same result because if you WERE being kept out of the rotation it does not take a genius to see this suituation happening from about 2 months back.<br>
<br>
  No one has explained to me yet just why the guilds in the rotation would keep Magister out of the rotation.  Sure, it adds another guild in.  But if we DON'T add them in, the whole system is flawed.  And then we get suituations like this, which help no one.  And to be brutally honest, what does 1 more guild matter when there are about 10 or so already in.<br>
<br>
  &lt;shrug&gt;  You could argue that Magister needed to prove themselves by beating a rostered guild to VS.  However, considering that there is no doubt at all that Magister is VS capable, I see no reason why that couldn't have been waived in this case.<br>
<br>
  In short, put away the Black Helicopters guys.  There was no conspiracy, it was a simple breakdown of communication.  Lets try to make sure it doesn't happen again. <br>
<br>
