Magister: You have the wealth of experience your older members bring with them. You are not, however, in the top two or three guilds in the game any longer.  You can make a compelling case that your aren't even the best guild on the server, but thats not the point I'm trying to make.  When you kill Yelinak, and Tormax, and clear North Wing of ToV, you're getting close. But you still won't be back at Da`kor levels, because thats all already been done, and with some regularity.  When I see someone with the Magister guildtag, if I recognize the name, I can be assured they probably are pretty capable. However, if I don't recognize the name, I wouldn't place them very far above any random person I meet in the game, because quite honestly, some of your new aquisitions used to be.... lets call them sub-par abilitywise(nothing wrong with that, if they've learned thats great, its just not up to the level Da`kor was at, which is what you asked).  <br>
